<script id="wix-first-paint">
    if (window.ResizeObserver &&
        (!window.PerformanceObserver || !PerformanceObserver.supportedEntryTypes || PerformanceObserver.supportedEntryTypes.indexOf('paint') === -1)) {
        new ResizeObserver(function (entries, observer) {
            entries.some(function (entry) {
                var contentRect = entry.contentRect;
                if (contentRect.width > 0 && contentRect.height > 0) {
                    requestAnimationFrame(function (now) {
                        window.wixFirstPaint = now;
                        dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('wixFirstPaint'));
                    });
                    observer.disconnect();
                    return true;
                }
            });
        }).observe(document.body);
    }
</script>


<script id="scroll-bar-width-calculation">
    const div = document.createElement('div')
    div.style.overflowY = 'scroll'
    div.style.width = '50px'
    div.style.height = '50px'
    div.style.visibility = 'hidden'
    document.body.appendChild(div)
    const scrollbarWidth= div.offsetWidth - div.clientWidth
    document.body.removeChild(div)
    if(scrollbarWidth > 0){
        document.body.style.setProperty('--scrollbar-width', `${scrollbarWidth}px`)
    }
</script>

wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">Al & Bea’s Mexican Food Restaurant opened its doors on November 15th, 1966 in the heart of Boyle Heights by Albert & Beatrice Carreon. </span></p>

<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"> </p>

<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">They opened with a simple dream of bringing their authentic homemade recipes to serve a community with a high demand for good genuine   Mexican food. Since that day in our history, the Green Chile and Refried beans have been making their mark ever since.   </span></p>

<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"> </p>

<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">As we look back in time, the word got out to hundreds of people who were anxious to taste the new authentic Mexican food from Al & Bea’s. The response was more than Al & Bea could have ever imagined. They set a new standard for Mexican fast food in the city of Los Angeles. </span></p>

<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"> </p>

<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">Since then, it has become a proud tradition that has created a loyal customer following that continues to be shared with others. Over the years, Al & Bea has never compromised taste, quality, or ingredients. To this day, generations of families who have been customers throughout the years can taste the same quality and flavor as their parents and grandparents did decades ago. </span></p>

<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"> </p>

<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">This November 2016, Al & Bea’s will be celebrating their 50th anniversary of the first day they opened their doors for business. They opened with nothing but high hopes and exceptionally good authentic recipes for Mexican food. 50 years later Al & Bea’s is still proudly family owned and operated.</span></p></div><!--/$--></div><!--/$--></div></section><!--/$--><!--$--><section id="comp-m8apbkco" tabindex="-1" data-block-level-container="Section" class="xuzjBY comp-m8apbkco
